NAME
	sysmon-svc (service) - poll /dev/memory, /prog/*/status, and /net conversation status at 1 Hz and rewrite current-snapshot and ring-buffer history files

INTERFACE
	service (MatrixService)

READS
	The mount parameter is unused; sources are absolute paths in the
	namespace the service is granted (compositions conventionally
	pass `service sysmon-svc /`):
	/dev/memory		pool statistics
	/prog/<pid>/status	per-process state and tick count
	/net/tcp/<conv>/status	connection state word
	/net/udp/<conv>/status	connection state word
	/net/tcp/stats		verbatim, where the platform provides it

WRITES	(to its outdir /tmp/matrix/sysmon-svc/ - mount a consuming
	display module there)
	mem/current	verbatim /dev/memory copy
	mem/history	ring: ts heap_cur heap_max main_cur main_max image_cur image_max
	cpu/current	pct busy_procs total_procs
	cpu/history	ring: ts pct
	proc/list	concatenated /prog/*/status rows
	proc/cpurates	one "pid pct" line per live process (tick delta per poll)
	net/current	"tcp total connected announced" and "udp ..." lines
	net/history	ring: ts tcp_total tcp_conn udp_total
	net/stats	verbatim /net/tcp/stats when non-empty

DESCRIPTION
	1000 ms poll; 60-sample shared ring emitted oldest-first.  CPU
	percent is derived from aggregate /prog tick deltas over elapsed
	wall time.  All files are replaced atomically (tmp file + rename),
	so readers never see torn writes.  Requires a whole-namespace or
	equivalent grant covering /dev, /prog, and /net.

SEE ALSO
	cpu-gauge, mem-gauge, net-gauge, proc-list (consume this outdir)
